【English】Abaton Privacy Policy
================================================================================

Abaton Privacy Policy

Your private data stays yours

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Overview
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Abaton (“the app”) is a mobile app focused on on-device privacy, developed and operated by an independent developer.

The app has no backend server and does not collect user data. Photos, videos, recordings, notes, and other content you store stay on your device only and are not uploaded or synced to any external server.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. We do not collect information
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The app does not collect, upload, or share information, including but not limited to:

• Private content such as photos, videos, recordings, and notes
• Passwords, PINs, or encryption keys you set
• Location, contacts, or call logs
• Device identifiers or advertising IDs
• Personally identifiable information
• Crash logs or error reports
• Usage analytics or behavioral tracking

The app does not include crash-reporting SDKs, ads SDKs, analytics SDKs, or social-sharing SDKs.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. System permissions
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The app may request the following permissions only for the stated features:

📷 Camera: capture photos/videos encrypted into the private vault; optional intruder alert may capture a photo after repeated wrong passcodes

🎤 Microphone: record audio for video or encrypted voice notes

🖼️ Photos: import from the system library into the vault or export vault items to the system library

The app does **not** request location permission on iOS or Android and does not access or collect your location. The items above are the only system permissions the app may request.

Content obtained through these permissions remains on your device. You can revoke permissions in system Settings at any time.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Network and in-app purchases
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The app uses the network only for in-app purchases (IAP): subscribing yearly or buying a lifetime unlock through Apple App Store or Google Play. Payment is handled entirely by Apple/Google; we do not receive your card details.

Aside from IAP, the app does not make other network requests.

Auto-renewing subscriptions:
• Charges are billed to your Apple ID / Google account
• Renewal occurs within 24 hours before period end unless you turn off auto-renew
• Manage or cancel in iOS Settings → Apple ID → Subscriptions or Google Play Subscriptions
• After cancellation, the current paid period remains active until it expires; refunds follow store policies

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. Storage and encryption
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
• Sensitive content is encrypted on-device (AES-256-GCM)
• Keys are derived from your numeric passcode and stored in secure hardware (iOS Keychain / Android Keystore)
• Uninstalling removes sandbox data; OS policies govern Keychain/Keystore entries after uninstall

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. Backup & transfer (.enc export / iCloud; cloud write iOS only)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
When you use in-app Backup & transfer to export a backup file with a .enc extension (zip payload inside) or save to iCloud, the following describes what is and is not included.

**Included (user data only):**
• Encrypted media inside the vault (photos, videos, recordings)
• Notes data

**Not included:**
• Any Keychain/Keystore credentials (unlock passcode material is not in the backup file)
• Any SharedPreferences data, such as language, UI preferences, camera resolution, or defaults for encrypting new items
• Local subscription or purchase flags, store revalidation timestamps, etc. (entitlements follow your Apple ID / Google account and store transactions; use Restore purchases as applicable)
• Separate folders such as intruder-alert captures (not packed into the backup; restore merges vault/notes only and does not delete existing local intruder-alert files)
• Other Keychain/Keystore entries not listed above (e.g., intruder-log master key)

**Handling and security:**
• Backup files use a .enc extension with a zip payload inside, without an extra app-level encryption wrapper; media inside remains in the app’s encrypted format. iCloud copies stay in your personal container
• Restoring merges vault and notes files only and does **not** change unlock credentials on the device; the file does not contain app settings or purchase flags
• You can turn off iCloud for the app or delete backups in system settings; .enc backup files shared by AirDrop, chat apps, etc. follow the same scope above

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7. Intruder alert
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Optional “intruder alert” can capture one front-camera photo after multiple wrong passcodes.

• Off by default; you enable it in Settings
• Photos are stored encrypted locally only
• Nothing is uploaded or sent to us

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8. Third-party services
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The app uses:

• Apple StoreKit / Google Play Billing for purchases (platform-managed; we do not handle payment details)
• Apple iCloud (optional) for backup file storage

No ads, crash analytics, behavioral analytics, or social SDKs are included.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9. Children
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The app is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect their personal information. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child used the app without consent, contact us using the details below.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
10. Your rights
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
• Delete data by uninstalling the app
• Export photos/videos to the system library when you choose
• Change your passcode anytime
• Revoke camera, microphone, or photo permissions in system settings
• Use core features without registering an app account (no cloud account system)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11. Contact
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
For privacy questions or requests, contact:

📧 Email: root4sec@gmail.com

We aim to respond within 7 business days.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
12. Updates
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This policy may change with app updates. The in-app copy will be updated; please review it periodically.

Material changes may be highlighted in the app. Continued use means you accept the updated policy.

